
@startuml

' Define classes based on system requirements

class University {
}

class Faculty {
    - name: String
}

class Institute {
    - name: String
    - address: String
}

class Employee {
    - socialSecurityNumber: String
    - name: String
    - email: String
}

class ResearchAssistant {
    - fieldOfResearch: String
}

class AdministrativeStaff {
}

class Project {
    - name: String
    - startDate: Date
    - endDate: Date
    - hours: Integer
}

class Lecturer {
}

class Course {
    - id: String
    - name: String
    - weeklyDuration: Integer
}

' Relationships

University "1" -- "0..*" Faculty : consists of
Faculty "1" -- "0..*" Institute : made up of
Faculty "1" -- "1" Dean : headed by
Employee "1" -- "1" Dean : is a dean

Employee "1" -- "0..*" ResearchAssistant : is a RA
Employee "1" -- "0..*" AdministrativeStaff : is an administrative staff

ResearchAssistant "1" -- "1..*" Institute : assigned to
Institute "1" -- "0..*" ResearchAssistant : has RAs

ResearchAssistant "1" -- "0..*" Project : involved in
Project "1" -- "1" ResearchAssistant : belongs to

ResearchAssistant "1" -- "0..1" Lecturer : can be a lecturer
Lecturer "1" -- "1" ResearchAssistant : is an RA
Lecturer "1" -- "0..*" Course : teaches

@enduml

---

### Notes:
- `University` contains multiple `Faculty`.
- Each `Faculty` contains multiple `Institute` and is led by one `Dean`, who is also an `Employee`.
- `Employee` can be either a `ResearchAssistant` or `AdministrativeStaff`.
- `ResearchAssistant` must be assigned to at least one `Institute`.
- `ResearchAssistant` can participate in multiple `Project`s.
- If a `ResearchAssistant` teaches courses, they are marked as a `Lecturer`.
- A `Lecturer` may teach multiple `Course`s.

